      <section eId="sec_580_105">
        <num>580-105</num>
        <heading>Application of the article to a resident of a foreign country and foreign support proceedings</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_105__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A tribunal of this state\nshall apply parts one through six of this article and, as applicable,\npart seven of this article, to a support proceeding involving:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_580_105__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>a foreign support order;\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_580_105__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>a foreign tribunal; or\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_580_105__subsec_a__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>an obligee, obligor, or child residing in a foreign country.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_105__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A tribunal of this state that is requested to recognize and\nenforce a support order on the basis of comity may apply the procedural\nand substantive provisions of parts one through six of this article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_105__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Part seven of this article applies only to a support proceeding\nunder the convention. In such a proceeding, if a provision of part seven\nof this article is inconsistent with parts one through six of this\narticle, part seven of this article controls.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
